cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on a quantitative study of Twitter communities and user influence, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also analyzes the data using influence measurement services, which could be considered a form of data mining (cs.SD) and social media (cs.SI).
